user tutorial:
* write 's' or 'S' to specify the end inserted pattern or stop the program at any
  other moment.

* specify first row and column of your pattern input:
  row: integer (1-512)
  column: integer (1-512)

* pattern input:
  0  			dead cell
  x,X,n,N		no change
  1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9 	live cell (number of generation cell can survive on its own)
  i,I			immortal cell
  e,E			mark the end of row
  s,S,q,Q		mark the end of pattern (and press ENTER)
  every other symbol is meaningless

	i.e.:	01e
		001e
		111s 
	to make a glider :)

* number of generations:integer (1-512)
			s ('S' or just 'stop' to stop the program)
